  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your chicken breasts into large chunks."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pop them in a bowl with 150g of your yoghurt, 1 tsp of your ground cardamom and a big pinch of salt. Give it a good mix, then pop in the fridge to marinate for a couple of hours."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel and slice your onion. Grate your garlic and ginger."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a glug of oil in a large pan over a medium heat. Add your cinnamon stick and onions to the pan, then fry for 10 mins until soft and starting to caramelise."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your garlic and ginger and cook out for 2 mins before adding your remaining cardamom, ground cumin, ground coriander, turmeric, chilli powder and tomato purée. Cook for a minute longer until fragrant."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Turn the heat right down. Tip your yoghurt, ground almonds, 300ml water and your chicken along with its marinade into the pan and bring to a gentle simmer. Add a good pinch of salt and pop the lid on – simmer for 20 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, toast your flaked almonds for a couple of mins in a dry frying pan until golden and fragrant. Chop your coriander."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once your cooking time is up, add your mango chutney to the korma and season to taste with salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serving time. Spoon your chicken korma over rice and sprinkle with your coriander and flaked almonds. Serve with rice or naan."
    }
  ],
